    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-09-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-09-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="369"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/6728</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        British Ambassador (<persName type="to">Halifax</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Secretary of State presents his compliments to the British Ambassador and
                    refers to Lord Halifax’ memorandum of September <pb facs="0383" n="377"
                        xml:id="pg_377"/> 12, 1942 regarding the shipment of supplies to French
                    North Africa.</p>
                <p>The Secretary of State takes pleasure in confirming that the contents of the
                    memorandum accurately set forth the position of the United States Government in
                    this matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-19">September 19,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
